'''Green Monday''' (GM) is a startup that makes low-carbon and sustainable living simple. Founded in 2012 in Hong Kong, GM is aimed at tackling [[climate change]] and ensuring [[food security]]. It is selected by FAST COMPANY magazine to be among China's Top 50 Most Innovative Companies of Year 2014.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}} In 2015, Green Monday launched “Green Common” in Hong Kong to empower the community with food choices that are sustainable, innovative, wholesome and responsible.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}

Green Monday cites references from the [[United Nations]] that livestock industry and factory farming are the number one contributor of the world's [[carbon footprint]].  Meat production also consumes a disproportionate amount of water and land resources, which directly jeopardizes [[food security]] and [[environmental sustainability]].{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}

As of 2014, results of a survey by market research company Ipsos showed that 1.6 million Hong Kong people, or 23% of the city's total population, embrace "Green Monday" - an increase of 18% from 2012,<ref name="China">{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/hkedition/2014-11/25/content_18970851.htm|title='Green Monday' backed by 1.6m fans|publisher=Chinadaily.com.cn|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref> and over 1,000 restaurants in Hong Kong are offering their menus.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}

==History==
Green Monday started to grow beyond Hong Kong in 2014. Events that marked their international recognition and growth include:  
* The [[University of Columbia]] became the first university in the US to launch Green Monday on their campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1HQew3aExHc|title=Green Monday at Columbia University!|work=YouTube|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref>
* [[Fast Company (magazine)]] named Green Monday among China's Top 50 Most Innovative Companies of Year 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fastcompany.cn/go.php?m=content&c=index&a=show&catid=17&id=2072|title=快公司中文网|publisher=Fastcompany.cn|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref>
* The US Consulate of Hong Kong, the [[American Humane Society]] and the Italian Chamber of Commerce in Hong Kong became Green Monday's partners.<ref name="China"/>
* Green Monday was launched at the [[Washington University in St. Louis]] in January 2015, becoming the second university in the US to join the program<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sustainability.wustl.edu/campus-operations/sustainable-dining/green-monday/|title=Sustainable Dining, Green Monday|accessdate=13 May 2015}}</ref>
* Green Monday's School Program has been sponsored by a local bank Charitable Foundation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bochk.com/ir/pdf/bochold/2013annual_report/ch14_e.pdf|format=PDF|title=Local Bank Annual Report 2013|publisher=Bochk.com|accessdate=5 January 2015}}</ref> As of 2014, More than 800 schools with about 600,000 students from kindergarten to university in Hong Kong pledged to observe "Green Monday".<ref name="China"/> From November 2012 to June 2013, the average vegetarian meal order rate increased from 4% to 42%.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}
* Major universities in Hong Kong, including the [[Chinese University of Hong Kong]], [[Hong Kong Baptist University]] and the [[Hong Kong University]] have also joined the Green Monday School Program.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}
* Outside Hong Kong,  [[Columbia University]], [[Washington University in St. Louis]], [[UCLA]] and [[Tsinghua University]] have launched Green Monday on their campuses.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}

==Criticism==
Although Green Monday is often compared with another movement [[Meatless Monday]], Green Monday insists that they simply want to create more plant-based options in the market and advise against removing conventional meat options.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}

